  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-05-06",
  "categories": [
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion and Development Updates",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "A key development announcement was made in the discussion channel: elizaOS and DegenAI have been added as the default payment method in elizaOS for x402 routes, receiving strong positive reactions from the community. Shaw also clarified that ElizaCloud has been consolidated into the main eliza repository on GitHub, migrated away from Vercel, and updated to support cheaper container infrastructure. The platform allows users to build and monetize their own apps on top of it.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778118536525-6w14b.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "Shaw addressed community concerns about the project's nature and token price, stating that elizaOS is a fair launch with no VC backing and no formal team structure. He explained that the project had to shut down its team model due to lack of profit, and that it now consists of builders using and building the technology. He also noted that founders are not responsible for managing token price, and warned that continued negative commentary would result in bans.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778118558615-1uhiwh.jpg"
        },
        {
          "text": "In the coders channel, a community member asked about the expected costs of running Eliza on cloud for a Twitter bot and whether it is possible to run on a Mac mini. Another user inquired whether elizaOS still connects to Hyperfy. A developer also offered their services to anyone needing development help. These questions reflect ongoing community interest in deployment options and integrations for elizaOS.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1300025221834739744",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1778118584422-4fu3o3.png"
        },
        {
          "text": "A community member shared a self-promotional post advertising AI and full stack engineering services, covering LLM systems, agents, RAG, multimodal, and automation work. Separately, a project called RubyHighAI was shared in the discussion channel, described as an AI-focused learning platform still in early development with some known bugs.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-thumbnail-1501613042813636668_e013e5b6.png",
          "videos": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-video-1501613042813636668_645dc6ad.mp4"
        }
      ],
      "topic": "discordrawdata"
    },
